PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777911069
OL,3,CSwans turning pink after being fed
OL,4,Cmouldy bread
OL,6,FLaura Ayres, a volunteer with
OL,7,FCaversham Wildlife Rescue and Support,
OL,8,Fsays the condition affects the swans'
OL,9,Fability to swim and can be fatal:
OL,10,F"Pink feather syndrome is the bloom of
OL,11,Fa fungus called chrysonilia sitophila
OL,12,Fwhich grows on decaying bread and
OL,13,Faffects birds that eat it.
OL,15,F"It goes on their feathers and it
OL,16,Fmakes them brittle, which can lead to
OL,17,Fhypothermia in winter time, or it can
OL,18,Fmake them less buoyant because their
OL,19,Ffeathers help with keeping them up."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777911069
OL,3,CSwans turning pink after being fed
OL,4,Cmouldy bread
OL,6,FAs part of efforts to educate the
OL,7,Fpublic, signs have been placed along
OL,8,Fthe promenade warning people of the
OL,9,Fdangers of mouldy bread.
OL,11,FGraham Neale, also from CWRS, has been
OL,12,Fpatrolling the area, and says they've
OL,13,Fseen a number of business owners
OL,14,Fflytipping in the river.
OL,16,F"About two months ago, one of our
OL,17,Fmembers caught a shopkeeper unloading
OL,18,Fhis car full of mouldy food, really
OL,19,Fmouldy and green and thrown in the
OL,20,Friver.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777911069
OL,3,CSwans turning pink after being fed
OL,4,Cmouldy bread
OL,6,F"And we know why they're doimg it
OL,7,Fbecause they've told us- because they
OL,8,Fhave to pay a private contractor to
OL,9,Fcome and take it away, and obviusly it
OL,10,Fcost them money."
OL,12,FReading Borough Council has been
OL,13,Fnotified of the incidents and says it
OL,14,Fwill take action against those
OL,15,Fresponsible.
OL,17,FMeanwhile, the charity is urging the
OL,18,Fpublic to keep feeding the swans.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
